  user_input {
    user_response: "Build a professional web app called \"SkyClear \342\200\224 Aviation Weather Briefing Tool\" \nfor PC and laptop browsers. This is a real utility tool for student pilots and \nlicensed pilots to decode aviation weather reports into plain English.\n\nTECH STACK:\n- React + Vite\n- Tailwind CSS\n- Dark aviation theme: background #0A0F1E (deep navy), \n  accent #38BDF8 (sky blue), warning #F59E0B (amber), \n  danger #EF4444 (red), success #22C55E (green)\n- Recharts for wind/visibility trend charts\n- Deploy-ready for Vercel\n\nLIVE DATA:\n- Fetch METAR data from: \n  https://aviationweather.gov/api/data/metar?ids={ICAO}&format=json\n- Fetch TAF data from: \n  https://aviationweather.gov/api/data/taf?ids={ICAO}&format=json\n- Both are free, no API key needed\n- Handle loading states and errors gracefully \n  (invalid ICAO, airport not found, API timeout)\n\n----- PAGES & FEATURES -----\n\n1. HOME / SEARCH PAGE\n- Full dark hero section\n- Large centered search bar: \"Enter Airport ICAO Code\" \n  (placeholder: WSSS, EGLL, KJFK)\n- \"Get Briefing\" button in sky blue\n- Below search: 4 quick-access buttons for popular airports \n  (WSSS, EGLL, KJFK, OMDB)\n- Tagline: \"Plain English weather for pilots. No decoder ring needed.\"\n- Footer: \"Built by [Name] \342\200\224 Student Pilot & Aerospace Engineering Applicant\"\n\n2. WEATHER BRIEFING PAGE (loads after search)\n\nSECTION A \342\200\224 METAR DECODER\nDisplay the raw METAR string at the top in a monospace code block.\nThen below it, decode every element into a clean card grid:\n\n- Station & Time card: \n  Airport ICAO, observation time converted to local + UTC\n  \n- Wind card: \n  Direction in degrees + compass (e.g. \"270\302\260 \342\200\224 From the West\"), \n  Speed in knots, \n  Gusts if present, \n  Calm wind detection,\n  Colour code: green if <15kt, amber if 15-25kt, red if >25kt\n\n- Visibility card: \n  Distance in SM and KM, \n  Plain English label: \"Excellent / Good / Moderate / Poor / Very Poor\",\n  Colour coded green/amber/red\n\n- Cloud Layers card: \n  Each layer decoded: coverage (FEW/SCT/BKN/OVC \342\206\222 plain English %), \n  Height in feet AGL and metres, \n  Cumulonimbus/Towering Cumulus warnings highlighted in red\n\n- Weather Phenomena card: \n  Rain, snow, fog, thunderstorm etc decoded from codes \n  (RA, SN, FG, TS, etc.) into plain English sentences\n  Show \"Clear \342\200\224 No significant weather\" if none present\n\n- Temperature & Dewpoint card: \n  Temp and dewpoint in \302\260C and \302\260F, \n  Dewpoint spread calculated, \n  Fog risk warning if spread < 3\302\260C (amber badge)\n\n- Pressure card: \n  QNH in hPa and inHg, \n  Standard pressure reference (1013.25 hPa)\n\n- Flight Category badge (large, prominent):\n  VFR = green, MVFR = blue, IFR = red, LIFR = purple\n  With plain English explanation of what each means for a pilot\n\nSECTION B \342\200\224 PLAIN ENGLISH SUMMARY\nOne paragraph summary of current conditions written in natural language.\nExample: \"Winds are light from the southwest at 8 knots. \nVisibility is excellent at 10 miles. \nA broken cloud layer sits at 3,500 feet. \nConditions are VFR \342\200\224 suitable for visual flight.\"\nGenerate this summary by combining the decoded fields.\n\nSECTION C \342\200\224 TAF DECODER (Forecast)\n- Show the raw TAF string in monospace block\n- Decode each BECMG / TEMPO / FM period into a timeline card\n- Each card shows: time period, expected conditions in plain English,\n  flight category badge\n- Timeline displayed horizontally as scrollable cards\n\nSECTION D \342\200\224 PILOT NOTES PANEL\nStatic educational sidebar panel with:\n- \"What is a METAR?\" one-paragraph explanation\n- Cloud base rule of thumb for fog formation\n- VFR minimums reminder\n- Link to full AIP (placeholder)\n\n3. ABOUT PAGE\n- \"SkyClear was built by [Name], a student pilot and \n  aspiring aerospace engineer, to make aviation weather \n  accessible for pilots at every level.\"\n- Tech stack badges\n- GitHub link (placeholder)\n- \"Part of my engineering portfolio \342\200\224 applying to Purdue, MIT, Stanford\"\n\n----- DESIGN RULES -----\n- Deep navy background throughout (#0A0F1E)\n- Sky blue (#38BDF8) for primary actions and highlights\n- Amber (#F59E0B) for warnings\n- Red (#EF4444) for danger/IFR conditions  \n- Green (#22C55E) for VFR/good conditions\n- All text white or light gray\n- Card-based layout with subtle borders (#1E293B)\n- Smooth loading skeleton while API fetches\n- Mobile-friendly but optimised for desktop\n- No emojis in the UI\n- Professional, clean \342\200\224 think aviation EFB (Electronic Flight Bag) aesthetic\n\n----- EXTRA DETAILS -----\n- Add a \"Refresh\" button that re-fetches live data\n- Show timestamp of last data fetch\n- If METAR is older than 2 hours, show a stale data warning badge\n- Handle all edge cases: \n  CAVOK condition, \n  variable wind direction (VRB), \n  vertical visibility instead of cloud layers,\n  military METAR format differences\n\nGenerate all files: App.jsx, all page components, \nall utility functions for METAR/TAF parsing, \nTailwind config, package.json, and a README.md \nexplaining the project for GitHub."
    items {
      text: "Build a professional web app called \"SkyClear \342\200\224 Aviation Weather Briefing Tool\" \nfor PC and laptop browsers. This is a real utility tool for student pilots and \nlicensed pilots to decode aviation weather reports into plain English.\n\nTECH STACK:\n- React + Vite\n- Tailwind CSS\n- Dark aviation theme: background #0A0F1E (deep navy), \n  accent #38BDF8 (sky blue), warning #F59E0B (amber), \n  danger #EF4444 (red), success #22C55E (green)\n- Recharts for wind/visibility trend charts\n- Deploy-ready for Vercel\n\nLIVE DATA:\n- Fetch METAR data from: \n  https://aviationweather.gov/api/data/metar?ids={ICAO}&format=json\n- Fetch TAF data from: \n  https://aviationweather.gov/api/data/taf?ids={ICAO}&format=json\n- Both are free, no API key needed\n- Handle loading states and errors gracefully \n  (invalid ICAO, airport not found, API timeout)\n\n----- PAGES & FEATURES -----\n\n1. HOME / SEARCH PAGE\n- Full dark hero section\n- Large centered search bar: \"Enter Airport ICAO Code\" \n  (placeholder: WSSS, EGLL, KJFK)\n- \"Get Briefing\" button in sky blue\n- Below search: 4 quick-access buttons for popular airports \n  (WSSS, EGLL, KJFK, OMDB)\n- Tagline: \"Plain English weather for pilots. No decoder ring needed.\"\n- Footer: \"Built by [Name] \342\200\224 Student Pilot & Aerospace Engineering Applicant\"\n\n2. WEATHER BRIEFING PAGE (loads after search)\n\nSECTION A \342\200\224 METAR DECODER\nDisplay the raw METAR string at the top in a monospace code block.\nThen below it, decode every element into a clean card grid:\n\n- Station & Time card: \n  Airport ICAO, observation time converted to local + UTC\n  \n- Wind card: \n  Direction in degrees + compass (e.g. \"270\302\260 \342\200\224 From the West\"), \n  Speed in knots, \n  Gusts if present, \n  Calm wind detection,\n  Colour code: green if <15kt, amber if 15-25kt, red if >25kt\n\n- Visibility card: \n  Distance in SM and KM, \n  Plain English label: \"Excellent / Good / Moderate / Poor / Very Poor\",\n  Colour coded green/amber/red\n\n- Cloud Layers card: \n  Each layer decoded: coverage (FEW/SCT/BKN/OVC \342\206\222 plain English %), \n  Height in feet AGL and metres, \n  Cumulonimbus/Towering Cumulus warnings highlighted in red\n\n- Weather Phenomena card: \n  Rain, snow, fog, thunderstorm etc decoded from codes \n  (RA, SN, FG, TS, etc.) into plain English sentences\n  Show \"Clear \342\200\224 No significant weather\" if none present\n\n- Temperature & Dewpoint card: \n  Temp and dewpoint in \302\260C and \302\260F, \n  Dewpoint spread calculated, \n  Fog risk warning if spread < 3\302\260C (amber badge)\n\n- Pressure card: \n  QNH in hPa and inHg, \n  Standard pressure reference (1013.25 hPa)\n\n- Flight Category badge (large, prominent):\n  VFR = green, MVFR = blue, IFR = red, LIFR = purple\n  With plain English explanation of what each means for a pilot\n\nSECTION B \342\200\224 PLAIN ENGLISH SUMMARY\nOne paragraph summary of current conditions written in natural language.\nExample: \"Winds are light from the southwest at 8 knots. \nVisibility is excellent at 10 miles. \nA broken cloud layer sits at 3,500 feet. \nConditions are VFR \342\200\224 suitable for visual flight.\"\nGenerate this summary by combining the decoded fields.\n\nSECTION C \342\200\224 TAF DECODER (Forecast)\n- Show the raw TAF string in monospace block\n- Decode each BECMG / TEMPO / FM period into a timeline card\n- Each card shows: time period, expected conditions in plain English,\n  flight category badge\n- Timeline displayed horizontally as scrollable cards\n\nSECTION D \342\200\224 PILOT NOTES PANEL\nStatic educational sidebar panel with:\n- \"What is a METAR?\" one-paragraph explanation\n- Cloud base rule of thumb for fog formation\n- VFR minimums reminder\n- Link to full AIP (placeholder)\n\n3. ABOUT PAGE\n- \"SkyClear was built by [Name], a student pilot and \n  aspiring aerospace engineer, to make aviation weather \n  accessible for pilots at every level.\"\n- Tech stack badges\n- GitHub link (placeholder)\n- \"Part of my engineering portfolio \342\200\224 applying to Purdue, MIT, Stanford\"\n\n----- DESIGN RULES -----\n- Deep navy background throughout (#0A0F1E)\n- Sky blue (#38BDF8) for primary actions and highlights\n- Amber (#F59E0B) for warnings\n- Red (#EF4444) for danger/IFR conditions  \n- Green (#22C55E) for VFR/good conditions\n- All text white or light gray\n- Card-based layout with subtle borders (#1E293B)\n- Smooth loading skeleton while API fetches\n- Mobile-friendly but optimised for desktop\n- No emojis in the UI\n- Professional, clean \342\200\224 think aviation EFB (Electronic Flight Bag) aesthetic\n\n----- EXTRA DETAILS -----\n- Add a \"Refresh\" button that re-fetches live data\n- Show timestamp of last data fetch\n- If METAR is older than 2 hours, show a stale data warning badge\n- Handle all edge cases: \n  CAVOK condition, \n  variable wind direction (VRB), \n  vertical visibility instead of cloud layers,\n  military METAR format differences\n\nGenerate all files: App.jsx, all page components, \nall utility functions for METAR/TAF parsing, \nTailwind config, package.json, and a README.md \nexplaining the project for GitHub."
