  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing Project Requirements**\n\nOkay, I\'m diving into the project requirements for \"SkyClear.\" Right now, I\'m performing a skill check to see what Google Cloud skills are needed. I\'ve already determined that cloudsql-execute-sql, cloudsql-setup, and cloudsql-update-schema aren\'t relevant to what\'s needed, as the project doesn\'t have SQL database requirements.\n\n\n**Eliminating Irrelevant Components**\n\nI\'ve determined that Firebase integration and focus mode are definitely not needed for this project. Moreover, I\'m confident that the Gemini API is also extraneous. I\'ve re-read the client brief, and the requirement is for a rule-based summary generator, which I can absolutely build with TypeScript. This approach keeps the tool client-side and snappy, and I will only consider using Gemini if an AI-based summary is specifically requested.\n\n\n**Refining Feature Scope**\n\nOkay, I\'ve just eliminated a huge list of skills and features as they\'re not needed for \"SkyClear.\" Gemini, GitHub integrations, Google Maps, image generation, OAuth, real-time features, and Shadcn UI are all out. I\'m focusing on the rule-based English generator, aiming for reliability and adherence to standard EFBs. I\'m confirming the three requested pages: Home, Weather Briefing, and About, ensuring strict adherence to the defined functional scope. The tech stack is React, Vite, Tailwind CSS, and Recharts, no extras.\n\n\n"
