  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing TAF Decoder**\n\nI\'m now diving into the construction of the TAF decoder. I\'m starting by analyzing the structure of a typical raw TAF message like KJFK 251130Z 2512/2618 24012KT 6SM -RA BKN030 TEMPO 2512/2515 5SM TSRA SCT020CB FM251800 27015G22KT 10SM BKN035 BECMG 2602/2604. I need to understand how to parse the different elements.\n\n\n**Analyzing TAF Structure**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on parsing periods within a TAF message. My strategy involves splitting the raw string based on period indicators like `FM`, `TEMPO`, `BECMG`. I\'m going to look for these keywords to break the text into chronological chunks. I am working on the function `decodeTAF(rawTaf: string, metarData?: DecodedMETAR): DecodedTAF` to handle this parsing. Currently, I\'m thinking of how to parse each period, and design a splitting mechanism to find these keywords, then split the text into chunks.\n\n\n**Defining Time Ranges**\n\nI\'ve been figuring out how to represent the time periods within the TAF messages. Specifically, I\'m working through parsing time indicators like `FM`, `TEMPO`, and `BECMG` to determine `timeStart` and `timeEnd` for each period. Then, I can parse wind, visibility, and clouds within these periods. It\'s becoming clearer how to handle the transitions. I\'m considering using the `decodeMETAR` function with some modifications.\n\n\n**Refining Parsing Strategy**\n\nI\'ve hit upon a brilliant strategy: code reuse! Each TAF period\'s core information (wind, visibility, clouds, weather) mirrors METAR syntax perfectly. I can prepend a standard METAR header, like \"KJFK 250000Z \", to each period text (after removing period prefixes), then feed it to the `decodeMETAR` function. It will flawlessly extract the necessary data, ensuring consistency and elegance, and allowing TAF decoding through METAR decoding. This simplifies the logic.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create `/src/utils/tafDecoder.ts` to implement the TAF (Terminal Aerodrome Forecast) decoder. It splits the TAF report into the base forecast and individual forecast periods (like FROM, BECMG, TEMPO, PROB30/40), and decodes each period by reusing the robust METAR parser logic. This ensures perfect alignment and prevents duplicate logic."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 6
      nanos: 99202281
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
