    thinking: "**Testing the Core Components**\n\nI\'ve made major strides! The METAR and TAF parser code is now complete. My next step is to generate a basic test index or file to ensure the parsers are functioning correctly. After this, I am considering whether to create `/src/utils/api.ts` to build out the querying function.\n\n\n**Exploring API Endpoints**\n\nI\'m now diving into the API endpoints. I have found the METAR and TAF endpoints and have begun testing them. Fortunately, `aviationweather.gov` API usually allows public CORS! In the interest of being ready for any environment, I\'m opting to build the client-side API fetcher in `/src/utils/api.ts`. I also made a test call with KJFK to verify the response.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will create `/src/utils/api.ts` to implement the live fetching mechanism. It pulls data from `aviationweather.gov`, sets up a 10-second timeout with an `AbortController` to handle slow/interrupted networks, handles empty responses for invalid ICAOs, and feeds the resulting raw text into our decoders. This maintains loading states and gracefully bubbles readable errors up to the UI."
