  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Constructing Briefing View**\n\nI\'m making excellent progress on `/src/components/BriefingView.tsx`. The main screen is coming together now to render the briefing data effectively. I\'m focusing on incorporating the requested features to make this briefing view robust.\n\n\n**Designing EFB Briefing View**\n\nI\'m structuring the briefing view in `/src/components/BriefingView.tsx` with a focus on an EFB-style layout. I\'m prioritizing the header elements, including the ICAO, refresh button, and timestamp. The stale weather warning badge is integrated. Next, I am working on the METAR decoder section, starting with a raw METAR display and subsequent card components: I\'ve started on cards for station data, wind, visibility, and cloud layers. I am currently working on implementing the color coding and data formatting for each of these cards, as described.\n\n\n**Adding Weather Data Components**\n\nI\'m now incorporating detailed weather components in the EFB view. I\'ve designed cards for weather phenomena, temperature/dewpoint (including fog risk warnings), and pressure. I\'ve built a prominent flight category badge that is fully operational now. I\'m focusing on color-coding for these cards based on the underlying data. I\'m also working on creating the initial plain English summary. Finally, I will tackle the TAF decoder section, including the Recharts requirement.\n\n\n**Implementing Trend Charts**\n\nI\'m making progress on the trend chart visualizations! I\'m constructing datasets from TAF periods for wind and visibility, aiming for clear line/area charts. The data will include time, wind speed/gust, and visibility. The wind chart will visualize wind speed/gust trends. The visibility chart will show visibility changes. I\'m excited about this pilot-friendly implementation! Now I need to work on the \"Pilot Notes Panel\" Sidebar.\n\n\n**Confirming Dataset for Trend**\n\nI\'ve confirmed the trend data can be calculated from `briefingData.taf.periods`. The data structure includes time, wind speed/gust, visibility, and flight category, making it perfect for charting. I also confirmed clean Recharts imports for `ResponsiveContainer`, `AreaChart`, and `Area` are possible, given the use of subcomponents. The dataset is extremely straightforward and perfectly tailored for charting. Now I\'m focused on the Pilot Notes Panel sidebar, section D.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now create `/src/components/BriefingView.tsx`. It features the standard aviation EFB (Electronic Flight Bag) layout:\n1. **Briefing Header**: Shows station, refresh buttons, retrieval timer, and stale-data indicators.\n2. **Flight Category Badge**: Displays VFR (green), MVFR (blue), IFR (red), or LIFR (purple).\n3. **Monospace Raw Blocks**: Shows the exact raw weather report.\n4. **Natural Summary**: Consolidates weather variables into an easy-to-read, natural paragraph.\n5. **Decoder Cards Grid**: Breaks down Station, Winds, Visibility, Cloud Layers, Weather Phenomena, Temp/Dewpoint spread, and Pressure.\n6. **TAF Forecast Horizon**: Displays chronological periods in a horizontally scrollable timeline.\n7. **Recharts Charts**: Renders two distinct charts (Wind Velocity trends & Visibility trends) to help pilots track incoming changes.\n8. **Pilot Notes Panel**: Static pilot-assistance sidebar.\nNo emojis are used in the UI, preserving a clean and professional cockpit appearance."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 7
      nanos: 365348462
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
