    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGpbVK_mSZ5wQTOVF_GnZiFU9GMn3_TpmQWFr8GksyVmmEfHA0OHvP9qO2PirGfx_gg76e5XYIlGexe2JWKSrlwo_1uxpxr2n6tONsS9O0nIBnptik7HJk6XciM1ifUH07y_r1sNthYx8MSEIU0oUdTA3DbuouNxZzXg3Z0a31c9oqOloJiNX33k0K_7gTwE3V8QI-HigvPyCJweVtdkFAMd68mLKxZVbVSpM-jVikqSw=="
      title: "medium.com"
    }
    summary: "The \"Uncaught TypeError: Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter\" error occurs in JavaScript when a script attempts to assign a new value to the `fetch` property of the `window` object, but `window.fetch` is configured as a getter-only property. This means the `fetch` function can be read from the `window` object, but it cannot be directly overwritten or reassigned[1][2].\n\nThis error typically arises in several scenarios:\n*   **Google AI Studio Development** Many users have reported encountering this specific error when developing applications within Google AI Studio, suggesting a potential interaction with the studio\'s environment or its underlying frameworks[3].\n*   **Third-Party Libraries and Polyfills** The error can be triggered by third-party JavaScript libraries or polyfills that try to redefine or shim the `window.fetch` function. If the browser\'s native `fetch` implementation is already present and set as a non-configurable getter, these attempts to overwrite it will fail[4][5]. For instance, similar errors have been observed with libraries like `gsap` in Next.js projects after version upgrades[4], with `axios` when bundled with `esbuild` due to its `follow-redirects` dependency[6], and with `vConsole`[5].\n*   **JavaScript Strict Mode** In some cases, running code in JavaScript\'s strict mode can make such property reassignments more prone to throwing errors[4].\n*   **Bundling Tools Conflicts** Issues can arise when JavaScript bundling tools process code that tries to redefine `fetch` in a way that conflicts with how modern environments handle the `window.fetch` property[6].\n\nTo debug and prevent this error, you should:\n*   **Identify the Source** Pinpoint the exact line of code that is attempting to set the `fetch` property on the `window` object[7].\n*   **Check for Library Conflicts** If using third-party libraries or polyfills for `fetch`, ensure they are compatible with the environment and don\'t conflict with a native `fetch` implementation. Consider updating libraries to their latest versions, as these issues may have been addressed[4].\n*   **Conditional Loading** If using a `fetch` polyfill, load it conditionally only when `window.fetch` is not natively available, to avoid overwriting an existing getter.\n*   **Review Environment Specifics** If developing in a specific environment like Google AI Studio, check its documentation for known issues or recommended practices regarding `fetch` usage[3].\n\nSources:\n[1] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEvqi0Lw8mS1MJGIWLJgII6WfeQnhie8wpbWG-vSAF1Wg3Mt9uREak2mvy4rqfePqwprdtQi-Ngb5FUiIRGPdlylQHqkqiucH41SN256vCsgiY_PdHtpIUv0TuFr9Yi-fCQ7713sLi4OdYFeWyxlLfdhJOUwOFCaj_Jr1rFYBk8FaziE4j82UF-CP0dyFDVSHsQrpgKeLmTMab8N7Kn3F-y)\n[2] [babylonjs.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGeaUDk44f18U1yLzWK5zxQyGmdmR6txNm9XrI5cMz2Q9mXQ7lhACP5Su627ODigkGcT2d-WMKXfMyWWt4R4NYM6KICuuTsybNpqHyK42rIkhRW5-zTdPf2uiz79bnKnxdTuuxDXWvNblxW7u7x7dfac6r3hqKO1-H-KyWUJp25YwMLhdiVS0g57CWXLoEh7rsjADzRldZ2jMHSjZ8T9eMzQtQAVfZosMk2uVBtig==)\n[3] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFfBkWn-J-dgBi_rLLH8yTUNYOsGqWDOUVg5904RMtwUTspRxuw89nf5KLHudcM0zB3oGb9OKg8K3wZaD6WeH7F7wZk7JqmtaUd3q-P76AQgEgWSKt_LenQVDnYQsBtVB6bn4p_U8n6efIuna6yr19nc38Pq7vIdr0lFQ3LN2iKoX7ATWexlfpcRB2yPVWk3xoj3Crzlgm_GhQaXaab7vhyF4XqUAvUTYVHUXEw4P6agw==)\n[4] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFYS8lMfWxsOeSJX4uUx_7DbgVqulKCt6EGkM5AUGgJwjCm5XZYbFpmsjK-8TJuEk1LUH8iWEwBq18Q1o51bKLZz6QOUasD8FalOa2TDPV2ltj2qZYDlNkzEDYPzV4C-vdTPFn2IPsloErERzD7BweR_tzzeHWlHJftLgs-llHFeaOpbzSnLKMTpA0R1i7utLjI2L6WYoshhedRpD5ijhfqynrpP1mUolblg7Ei1ObHTn1W)\n[5] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGQKUP4an84X4jY4FARpRe-qS0PTVl_Gi_rrpgxzthAAw5YoqKtM3_G8bEnCtJHWsT8K92org7hH44ksut3kKTwXqAtfbVvxow