      title: "stackoverflow.com"
    }
    summary: "The error \"Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter\" indicates that you are attempting to assign a new value or function to `window.fetch`, but `window.fetch` is a read-only property of the `Window` object in JavaScript[1][2][3][4]. This error commonly occurs in strict mode.\n\nWhile you cannot directly reassign `window.fetch`, there are several techniques to intercept or override its behavior if you need to modify requests, log information, or mock responses:\n\n1.  **Using a `Proxy` Object**\n    You can create a `Proxy` around the original `window.fetch` function. This allows you to intercept calls to `fetch` and execute custom logic before or after the original `fetch` is invoked[5]. The `apply` trap of the `Proxy` is used to intercept function calls.\n\n    Example:\n    \n\nSources:\n[1] [geeksforgeeks.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHfcHP5KXHpIzlXe5twyidbX1Xxv_5mgw75P5tj-P0XgHa7fk_MpHxguCfM_1Nvz0BgIInz2sc-3FFP3oG4IRzudysQa8zr-9wI0ywdtMgKrhq912lX1sDf-f6mwoFBdfTNluxPkNHDw1A8pdPIonmWwTmZJuB9V9K3_rP--XUlktCsNa7M91Nlv8bfsVSzLAAB8Ji4bK4J)\n[2] [mozilla.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEa2zYJKro_R7AMYS7gLV9EN9yv_BiJu8OZOloTiTClwtDiczbh4XRAU2JnLkTGi2KepgN4T1VMo-geCfXo4G2H_dhs0mF98r7h3ZhEK71fYAIy--h47dmbUbhhGpkC1JxnGd1NiDXbBCUcOcToezFb4yLG-Fh4KNPlZDJz1zDy0MSfUs6LW5MzVI1qFRmm)\n[3] [realityripple.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEO07svzKccQ9HJqhi1tzpk66_lROh1BkDkeOsf9qj9mYV7hml29tkkw2ancxySKjGJb_xS_TOuwmShVGQsWm6g9msdQl2UlxOeNjEDzInwOahdffEqe7ZR95iczva7UyuC2-mZUgbPlpoDtQvcfqAlcPa0O39_ZBeHDETH7fnF5QXVBJmgNyN9)\n[4] [zipy.ai](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFHUJ9QzlE94DLkaBEdEdIsdYpl7xFujboP2x-tzHjowktWx1ZNZ2edrljkbEVlut3HlgmDcua0WVSGs0liVkD2r1HEO0lHghZKwW7UQT91CF6VD2HhfP0syyddanwE_VplnZR5ZHvkbTSfRyEHAA8znFy0slXJ3hBy6y7-AqN6)\n[5] [dev.to](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.