    summary: "The error message \"TypeError: Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter\" indicates that you are attempting to assign a new value to the `fetch` property of the `Window` object, but this property is read-only and cannot be directly overwritten. In JavaScript, a \"getter-only\" property means you can retrieve its value, but you cannot set it to a new value[1][2][3].\n\nThe `fetch()` method is a built-in Web API function provided by the browser\'s `Window` interface, used for making network requests[4][5]. Because it\'s a fundamental browser API, directly reassigning `window.fetch` is disallowed to maintain consistency and prevent unexpected behavior.\n\nThis error commonly occurs in the following scenarios:\n\n*   **Testing and Mocking:** When writing unit tests, developers often try to \"mock\" the `fetch` API to control its behavior and prevent actual network requests. In testing environments like Jest or Vitest, directly assigning to `global.fetch` (which represents `window.fetch` in a Node.js-based test environment) can trigger this error if not done correctly[6][7][8][9].\n*   **Monkey Patching:** Attempts to intercept or modify the global `fetch` behavior at runtime, sometimes referred to as \"monkey patching,\" can lead to this error if the approach involves a direct assignment to `window.fetch`[10].\n*   **Strict Mode:** While some attempts to set getter-only properties might be silently ignored in non-strict JavaScript, in strict mode (which is often implied in modern JavaScript modules and classes), such an action will explicitly throw a `TypeError`[1].\n\n### Solutions and Workarounds\n\nTo address this `TypeError`, consider the context in which you are trying to modify `fetch`:\n\n1.  **In a Testing Environment (e.g., Jest, Vitest):**\n    *   **Use Testing Framework\'s Mocking Capabilities:** Instead of direct assignment, leverage the mocking utilities provided by your testing framework.\n        *   For Jest, you can often mock global functions using `jest.fn()` and `mockImplementation()`. For example, `global.fetch = jest.fn(() => Promise.resolve({ json: () => Promise.resolve(mockData) }));` is a common pattern[7][9].\n        *   For `node-fetch` (a common `fetch` polyfill in Node.js environments), you would mock the `node-fetch` module itself rather than `global.fetch`[11].\n    *   **Use a Fetch Mocking Library:** Libraries like `fetch-mock` can provide more comprehensive and controlled ways to mock HTTP requests in tests[8].\n\n2.  **For Runtime Interception (e.g., in a browser for debugging or custom behavior):**\n    *   **Avoid Direct Reassignment:** Since `window.fetch` is getter-only, you cannot directly assign a new function to it.\n    *   **Use a Dedicated Interception Library:** Libraries like `fetch-intercept` are designed to allow you to intercept and modify `fetch` requests and responses without directly reassigning the global `fetch` function[10].\n    *   **Proxy-based Solutions (Advanced):** More advanced techniques might involve using Proxies to wrap the `window` object or the `fetch` function itself, but this is considerably more complex and usually not necessary for common use cases.\n\nThe core principle is to use methods that are designed to work with read-only properties or to mock the underlying module/function in a controlled environment, rather than attempting to directly overwrite a protected browser API.\n\nSources:\n[1] [mozilla.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHggxobQU_UTTbuylg39nYndR7b1F5xsDvuJHXKHcauraDwWRnxVFOzn1D3NYW2tPYwKKpr4RvE1kz-1XTm0eqcbWPOA2oBjsuhQNZSjng8-8g4SikBRbHzYIePks89M96LN28-Ad_D8vV17thQ8akA0PbrBOq71L1nxuMtJaMPO6XJJ-OwqE2N3999YmyW1A==)\n[2] [bobbyhadz.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEAwc6qU6mfcM90DpuTZRs7mG10LoUo96ulhdY7iuS4E21247ZH3DKTwr1Sxqm9m8IA45q5iafvhiASZ-ZHupOr54Uh3ITKokq-2qiXqSlUuWutcHBSohdjly6HEpsZ7t6eVq1l2IYpGn9bOQvYRh-3UHBTcTa7IVaGEPgbuTymr-CZ9dBBprSYUhE=)\n[3] [geeksforgeeks.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFa74FQ7bqBlWzy2wgg_PnloK8nlbhg0Xb6MgRPF-WY6tEwwu6nlVIiffxF4w8HeDnbjB8PCEhLQBNOeBdG8ird-6Pnpp1VjCTmz-mNGy1MP6vljbaI1sMmdQkg_naVtUA3u19k52mU43SMcOy00vu3j-1PBgnLaLiorNtEEpNXDJyboQ==)\n[4] [mozilla.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFCaj382269RVMdkNLCAnf58LlYKkJrloG-LN8_H_QRib2hp-ueCGWLZiFDdMJIKIf-f_3b8CZaj26BDVAjg_mnIsRIXHCAMzAPG80AdK7lMCUgyDYSL7PW12by6gDBSkc3bvlG2hJkdN19LrTajVYAFfLYsByp_kc=)\n[5] [mozilla.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGmq3tdyljijFIXTF2ZsLGqnDk7K3fKN8Fl1RjVW1pXb68BCTlbEXq5HpM7Mjc3O_349pJv8F4dfck_cxMZRtYSLUYuR9acTNy47U9ibbHAAlwIlqLc24_m36x-w158DYu37Cak0uW4V06pVE3FA6A2FZkss_1Tq0BSqe-o4IS_fxE=)\n[6] [adropincalm.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG6Wq-l3eSsC_OYjoG7yziEOKP_qOBGMT4zs3SAjWqG8vygzXHFBmnevZd0srMrxDs8OnLPtEXFk6jMRPVvlzxFsT8ub1wJqzthbdSPGweqv5DmVXixEy51H4HJNFhcro3rBLL8I177cX0hBjKhq2yuBzLXGemzTL3KF2aCKzre8JVM2To=)\n[7] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHGkBO5qiEW_6j6ILp5lgpMwHgna5L8-DAOuhugBRswE6awgMh-VjqhOIiWBUeKrc0TX7JKVAmqSMd0BEh7UvQd99VP57LMi03ymEK1xlSjSI_IQRuw_8FuFTBV5gFrdqulSW9kGjkMbIEZZ2Xq3qeKtnXRO0dbtJoOzWZ6IOp3Bb-IwfWx4Ab7KBdWhio=)\n[8] [swizec.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGUoARL6Itw_eHwnwjuI-dHaopwZUw3yFAy1JB6do0GUI0DLqj2CT8yoS-RVRgsc6qJbJv7kdvIKlNFTEsE_V1T_3gco2dyVW6RTZboSrMOLRyP4auVnKLr7fUUrlWze4wFwkkx8pb7xblgnAgEdOsdraYizgVLGSPFT9sW1vdubA==)\n[9] [stevekinney.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHT_sn0WYWZsKVCElh2lZb8Mck5NahjQQkFXgRBzcw2y1U34ds0SgpEyPMdD9eZmy5VGNIIk-LlXRwPnUtcL_6QDC7aZOPpW-k-NNL9V_0OOZhfpYJOarQvrPfj_0R1Nv7aPICsUl31sO5RZtKVu6LdZJAzV2RCvsA422CFnPPjgb4EbQ7B)\n[10] [logrocket.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGI-BQQC_YWcZEYmjOpf5gcMxvPGGYkT733dgLr2VDSU-kPCjem74louC1Pe_ly-ko8B2ePn6gcvHdiA_AzQ0Uj3sQO3txSrA_BfOcl2wAbi5IRKFuePNO7RQ-XwM4KnfM4HEII_7rvTUFR6Hj17DLT4bQsIfGgRC3vCg521I1nqCG5xJBpiZr-IsiZ)\n[11] [dev.to](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQH-s28PqQm-zRUC5eDYf8gH7Q0dWp0Y1fMtVd8_L00o_GkvUtLqmX7a7aU4lxIFVutz3oT59Wm0VS4HkxI3OiX7pt-1OAWWJV6P4EJfi4UIPPyHahLWSzLaB_dY_Ht9j7h5iXzBgSRf5NNUNC7KYWsRP0T7zwKiWLC5fY54Y8LPNn_wGhM3iowwLcI=)"
