    summary: "The error message \"Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter\" typically occurs in JavaScript when you attempt to directly reassign the global `window.fetch` method, which is defined with only a getter and is therefore read-only[1][2][3].\n\nThis `TypeError` is often encountered when developers try to \"monkey patch\" or intercept the `fetch` API to add custom functionality, such as logging, authentication, or caching for network requests[4][5][6][7]. In strict mode, which JavaScript classes always use, attempting to set a getter-only property will throw this error[1].\n\nTo properly override or add hooks to the `fetch` API, consider these approaches:\n\n*   **Using a `Proxy` object**: The recommended method for intercepting `fetch` requests is to use a JavaScript `Proxy`. A `Proxy` object allows you to create a proxy for another object, enabling you to intercept and redefine fundamental operations for that object. By wrapping `window.fetch` in a `Proxy`, you can add custom logic before or after the original `fetch` call without triggering the \"getter\" error[4].\n    *   For example, you can use the `apply` trap of a `Proxy` to intercept when the `fetch` function is called[4].\n*   **Saving and reassigning (with caution)**: While direct reassignment often causes this error, some implementations save the original `fetch` method to a constant and then reassign `window.fetch` to a custom function that internally calls the saved original. This method requires careful implementation to avoid the getter error[5][7].\n*   **Service Workers**: For more robust network request interception, especially for features like offline support and advanced caching strategies, Service Workers are a powerful solution. They operate as a proxy between your web application and the network, allowing you to intercept and handle requests programmatically[6].\n\nSources:\n[1] [mozilla.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFcd7bEJb8NiLFXbopWc2Hfx-76QIvZVcqedw38clZuwkxUKQpfFzaFJ91SYVlDRbNUZa6CqJ8p410kG97e3_3pa-o-KmpT79H138P51eU7heyf9GY0Pi68Lt1NPwdgJcodxN6DI9KAckiDoFKZQcA3enaNAX3fmK1E83_jCzi8dyDzUSQqTPx0yuTxcOAcxw==)\n[2] [geeksforgeeks.org](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEX2JKJCZN2oCv4jSAK-fdrGRp--nXQrKM670NGIFK9xzmkD54JivlZezsBm8Ky6-HXLz5nZma4KwozB8U6NwVTD5oE0hnnMjXHHUN2u3BZwAeE4TGdAb3Wc5Oh1hqXpGqxyt7q5J12MfRgu5AyNFA8AEWmrHXbk_MhWxR12ZeASTrtRPTY1k_Vvr_yhe-4O4n9X5p8zG0zTg==)\n[3] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEiPL_20TwAeBrFxuI7ObA-LVNnPHGv_j5n4LZW9wn_rubgU6NUnCjMcUqI3nzgM_2WGz1_i87hxXp0OnvDCN_-9skkR3s15I-gORv_faZJlqHYACrU3HFT9fdxpbrsNlKZ9zGw7YqleTteLH9MYUxUsSiYlspcpC09qpOuZ3Ihdy3rv-2WSMIhLW_jNkUJbn1op-chBRTNGA9oGRxya54fv2w45jKpKYKavU6cBEYtEw==)\n[4] [dev.to](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFYE4H7rUgmc0nk6FkiMhakOrvehsY2zu7mTop-sIFymmWmnxyOjFZ5wIGhp63miOVGNCi0Qm0ENQU4Ci-Jx46u8ITU-ZcmdKmCcpbRKCCFXgY6H5pBbjZuTZLtQV45elT_QhJdk3DUv2eFp8Jwx7Y4HK1fDifpFn4AJlz6q7RABxNcEGCg)\n[5] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGmzHqoSOIb1GlyPuy1-3oEECG027wFhM9apoa5tB-2Lc0448Z-zAQnlvDyNKlAInfu1eZvS_ciTnT1Y32eUAOg68suegB-f7TSknT6EjJXzWV3bE_xcV1kr3ZBy5nPHV1btI2fKe-t6EXwMxH87F-BZ0ft2Dx4bdkxnOaAbbYPuAuyvMQzTxIh8KL6iIkK)\n[6] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFsqYSjg6JVfEFW57Mr-3CDe4SRumfyaDYjHF294MxM-rHBIqfi4etNw3B2eGhn3ocQmehR26_NwcxgJwW-vcNotueBMhZ-zSg-pjar567f8Ulp8McghZDCR0dVac41fjQyeUTdxHmxybvLRMXKSGsyxGpwy_k1xxs=)\n[7] [logrocket.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHo8SIKcejtA0qdgPxvdx71ifsIFPRAZUtocUIff64gihcgSir3exx38lJuP_N3brleNZBGH-7ulAcPcUfIx9ad1YAMbJvYXbeJ20pLCIKJPRAsMgKwIgRDbxZ5q2TTTrvq_JLXbYyyrngxd-8LG-UUVd9KU5mvE1QqPV7YRDtOFYAnXus3L0ST3Qit)"
