    web_documents {
      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG8uo3W-_xKGTAKoAcRCaiCRw4BJh7yp7oTRZP3gfHfDypOSrp4DkAQdED6QvbpweR3D2m_HX8RPYEzrcTklPFMhmqsYsYIpcKNwO5T7N3qh5injyrycIxLnd4kMMlM67WgAH87Zq3hZGkmIzXCiyU-52Bs2cTxi-ON2oXt2GTg4HzZTv7ibUg2OLs7AhpC_1ECptwhzSRAsfDaQJ1DbDH-TjxQf-ltaaWtyfUskdgKr0-LYA9EGIBYnDmYWXTCxaVS7Q=="
      title: "google.dev"
    }
    domain: "stackoverflow.com"
    summary: "The search for \"Cannot set property fetch of\" site:stackoverflow.com revealed several discussions, primarily on GitHub issues and related forums, indicating that the error \"Uncaught TypeError: Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter\" is a common problem when attempting to reassign `window.fetch`.\n\nThe error typically occurs because `window.fetch` is a read-only property in modern browsers, meaning it cannot be directly overwritten[1]. This often happens when a library or application tries to proxy or modify the native `fetch` function without properly checking if the property is writable[1].\n\nSolutions and workarounds often involve:\n*   **Checking Writable Property:** Before assigning, verify if the `fetch` property is writable using `Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor()`[1]. If it\'s not writable, the assignment should be skipped or handled differently[1].\n*   **Using `globalThis` for ESM:** In ES Modules (ESM), directly assigning `this.fetch = customFetch` can lead to this `TypeError`. Instead, `globalThis.fetch = customFetch` is the correct way to modify the global `fetch` in ESM environments, as `globalThis` provides a consistent way to access the global object[2].\n*   **Issues with Specific Libraries/Platforms:** Some users have encountered this error in the context of specific tools or platforms, such as `vConsole` (where it was reported that `vConsole` directly executed `window.fetch = ...` during initialization, causing the error)[1] and Google AI Studio[3][4]. In such cases, the issue might be with the library or platform\'s implementation, and updates or specific configuration might be required.\n*   **Incognito Mode for Debugging:** One suggestion for debugging this error is to try reproducing it in an incognito window, which can help rule out issues caused by browser extensions[3].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEnF32NPLIrxtWJd4YGjeZrCcqD8Hx0U-fpntVNituhbI1RFC01hzXjxufoWs4ZNGbtRyT8_IDwl0cLc3uZhAB9vp_gp0DgOUuz4--3KhV9n-wKtwAPhEISPS7fmTwWOciRmUQm1IcTjA==)\n[2] [csdn.net](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFffqy0lT2QAyLv9gsg3aVBQ3hbib8PDJEX2QJPfk4q7UzqE1doWdV-c90oAYoEp2BvnPWNNP66kJKGP3ZkIpJsl-LWkGy5mEQBJMQ1vedTmwg9XSRdImsnn52JQtWtRcRUYEsvkkbouMYkVXFyP32Tmlj-fCM8KA==)\n[3] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEaCn1YWFpjMrITIi-V86kPxZ9pEWHPKTY_P8oTk33REHuG3bGyV_qlkAyvgWUI9_J7OFdaG2Fy-78PVWWAfmw1U8yM3yVIiHFvlDVqVUU8Jh06IKnxP12j_QPaYVUYzN0VtbFnqMcOsshM-SkNs3B5eyRmkfsRMEgWwyq7AH3Ru0zMhUbFqbf7KOXzYJthmTipTJAIOXETRXZbfNlmKMYC-65GQ_aDP_F1FeEz5fx4)\n[4] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG8uo3W-_xKGTAKoAcRCaiCRw4BJh7yp7oTRZP3gfHfDypOSrp4DkAQdED6QvbpweR3D2m_HX8RPYEzrcTklPFMhmqsYsYIpcKNwO5T7N3qh5injyrycIxLnd4kMMlM67WgAH87Zq3hZGkmIzXCiyU-52Bs2cTxi-ON2oXt2GTg4HzZTv7ibUg2OLs7AhpC_1ECptwhzSRAsfDaQJ1DbDH-TjxQf-ltaaWtyfUskdgKr0-LYA9EGIBYnDmYWXTCxaVS7Q==)"
