    summary: "The error message \"Cannot set property fetch\" often indicates an attempt to redefine or modify the global `fetch` object when it is configured as a read-only property or when conflicting `fetch` implementations are present. This issue commonly arises in projects using Vite or React due to several factors:\n\n*   **Polyfill Conflicts** The `fetch` API may not be natively supported in all browser environments, especially older ones like Internet Explorer 11. Developers often use polyfills like `isomorphic-fetch` or `whatwg-fetch` to provide `fetch` functionality[1][2]. The error can occur if an incorrect polyfill version is used (e.g., a Node.js-specific polyfill in a browser environment) or if multiple polyfills conflict with each other[1][3].\n*   **Vite and Node.js Module Polyfills** Vite, by design, does not automatically polyfill Node.js modules for browser code[4][5][6]. If a third-party library or dependency within a Vite or React project relies on Node.js-specific `fetch` implementations or global objects that interact with `fetch`, it can lead to this error[4][5]. Vite\'s documentation suggests avoiding Node.js modules in browser code or manually adding necessary polyfills[4][5].\n*   **Library Conflicts and Proxies** Certain development tools or libraries, such as `vConsole`, might attempt to proxy or redefine the `window.fetch` object. If `window.fetch` is already defined as a read-only getter property by another script or the browser, these attempts will fail and trigger the \"Cannot set property fetch\" error[7][8][9][10][11].\n*   **Google AI Studio/Gemini API Interaction** Users developing applications with Google AI Studio and interacting with the Gemini API have also reported encountering this specific error. This suggests potential environmental or platform-specific interactions that might be attempting to modify `fetch`[8][12][13].\n\nTo troubleshoot this error, consider checking for conflicting polyfills, examining third-party dependencies that might be attempting to redefine `fetch`, and ensuring that polyfills are correctly configured for the target browser environment within your Vite or React project.\n\nSources:\n[1] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGXsNcELKUAgAhRjIP1LIjYCg97NKa6xUz1snPZb73ePQCkAjzoYn788vpx4v0o3_87WYUaztcQwQ5CfsERL3mjzyiFV5cmiz0KDFBbvLhfWEylulM8avj1SzUJMULua-ytfS_e8hibxvLmffT4Jvzobiu6UlUreZj2YCMBagDe_ugivYH9YwajmezUMx1wz7dCA2jnzF8r-pz1LCvaDlE=)\n[2] [dev.to](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQG6oQ6mBl1OKilqKulEdvEnQ3dY3nOQKqFCr_gocxP2UAj-xmtKyXGUcgMjYwpKnbWFHHessyjhT4wQVNhpJB2se3BklFIq0wxCL-yqKdFHBmLn7CV9gSdBb_XaA3N70U03QCf6MLrdeZLIE_cmFmfunXSH6gnyU_AKuJmb662BG6W9X43jJbJtay7XUauZ-Q==)\n[3] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFFAjlUcmuRmvX-LeVXG9F_wy5t2TjqhEsoW-VnUqtcHdBbh8LIWcNV84rq3rbeqsA-HXRBp5IILJt4GgjdwYAK_sCE2P8UQSUQAUY7KlgUgeNsQmFzgkVUsk0xS-GvI3wXT71Zcp161NeKo20cqOWSqsSoeK4F33nLjAyRI02_JxS1UGrXRPEst8sNvjMn7hy5IeCS9HDYWTWqd1lxRjL87jueeirhJHDb6DxBE8QBXjqChmrCvg==)\n[4] [vite.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEkCTkkphwyKythKG2zlXlchm9CVjYxrRixUrbzwm9nsPJh_6k_flTRUP1ho8Ikm_gsQViPHrjGWcvx7Tq4SNeVBvKRc2O-cG1UkFLSoCIIpIe2MXMOhfkj0KN13lAbXjk6)\n[5] [metamask.io](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHpuUI1DhvrpXsLBvbC3F6sLnpOZVbUixzWRVGtOIWalguS5t6EC1TYL2ylgllshoa8nr_J6UwZRffYwKnkB4uwJ0wGqunCDBBrN1UHAwvYV3ceqvdMXEs2d2qv2Qt-9eIrNyWwC9DhR-hcCGaluJSOfGuHfk_-AKHXrOzCf2x5fg0=)\n[6] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEoC-jeKg_hgU__rAyw-FJ3mDHSHKNmd9UjSpTNnDvlMYt8clDvURFz_6U7o96j-L1GHwuPyaVl8wp5-GacBLciBCn5H_BFbX5zhgc_vDe3aUBNLSNy9Ky7UeqeKmrOigJZAyooOPs=)\n[7] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGENZACtFy-1NaO8g2A2WMhKqPi3HhxqpjSxRjAuDxXPz3olXN_3haWqfYPaiGvRM3tXgBlkHhhynPiwPWWXrj