r.\n\n\n**Pinpointing Package Integration**\n\nI\'m now investigating how the `node_modules` are integrated. There is a potential conflict and I am going through the dependencies in `package.json` to find possible offenders. Specifically, `@google/genai` is a suspect since it is a dependency that could try to polyfill `fetch`, since it supports both browser and Node.js environments. I\'ve rechecked that, despite being listed, the package is not actually imported in our client-side code, so Vite does *not* bundle it.\n\n\n"
