      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF_FHY6Pcp3uto3c2ygAllFtl4sTpr9yZs3C165VMLX8syYFk4q3SIGPQM5-qTUnzce9OL3gJQUtOF1lh9yhRmQSJGd7BQooy35ttBHJH5eNbEqkAsFuVPr0wx8M5AihmoNraTBSEFhtCpx3hErG0RNcJHZP_qkSaKkOKSN54WDbdsvQRouMG4TxW_fmfPlg6yevHcq6rAJWH2Mce1PKwbiL73P0hzd1eD3mYjuZffU28HJ"
      title: "stackoverflow.com"
    }
    summary: "The error message \"Cannot set property fetch of #<Window>\" or \"Cannot set property fetch of Window\" in JavaScript indicates that you are attempting to reassign the `fetch` method directly on the `window` object, which is generally not permitted because `window.fetch` is a read-only property or has only a getter[1][2][3]. This means its value cannot be directly changed like a regular variable.\n\nThis error commonly arises in a few scenarios:\n\n*   **Direct Reassignment:** Trying to assign a new function or value to `window.fetch` directly, like `window.fetch = myCustomFetchFunction;`[4][5].\n*   **Testing and Mocking:** Developers often try to replace `window.fetch` in testing environments (e.g., using Jest or Vitest) to mock API responses and avoid actual network calls[4][5][6]. While direct assignment might lead to this error, testing frameworks provide specific ways to mock `fetch`.\n*   **Third-Party Libraries or Polyfills:** Sometimes, a third-party library or an older polyfill might attempt to redefine `window.fetch` in an incompatible way, especially if the environment has a native `fetch` implementation[2][7][8].\n*   **Browser Extensions/User Scripts:** Scripts attempting to intercept or modify `fetch` behavior might encounter this if they don\'t use the correct methods for overwriting built-in browser functions[9].\n\n**Solutions and Workarounds:**\n\n1.  **Mocking for Testing:**\n    *   **Jest:** You can use `jest.spyOn(window, \'fetch\').mockImplementation(...)` to mock `fetch` in Jest tests[4][10]. Remember to clean up mocks after each test (e.g., with `afterEach(() => { jest.restoreAllMocks(); })`).\n    *   **Vitest:** Vitest allows you to mock `fetch` by setting `global.fetch` within your test setup, for example, `global.fetch = vi.fn(() => Promise.resolve(...))`[5]. Vitest also has `vi.clearAllMocks()` for cleanup[5].\n    *   **Dedicated Mocking Libraries:** Libraries like `fetch-mock`[6][11] or `msw (Mock Service Worker)`[10] are designed to intercept and mock network requests, including `fetch`, more robustly without directly reassigning `window.fetch`. MSW, for instance, works by creating a mock server that intercepts requests[10].\n\n2.  **Intercepting `fetch` (with caution):**\n    If you need to intercept `fetch` outside of a testing environment, directly reassigning it is problematic. Instead, consider:\n    *   **Storing and Calling the Original:** You can store the original `window.fetch` in a variable, then redefine `window.fetch` as your custom function, and inside your custom function, call the original `fetch` when needed. However, this approach is still subject to the \"Cannot set property\" error if `fetch` is not configurable.\n    *   **Using `window.eval` (for user scripts):** In some user script contexts (like Tampermonkey), `window.eval` might be necessary to execute code within the page\'s context to successfully override `window.fetch`[9].\n\n3.  **Understanding \"Illegal Invocation\" (related error):**\n    A related error, \"Failed to execute \'fetch\' on \'Window\': Illegal invocation,\" often occurs when `fetch` is called with `this` not bound to `window`[12]. This can happen if you extract `fetch` from the `window` object and call it as a standalone function or as a method of another object. The solution is to use `.bind(window)` to ensure `fetch` is called with the correct context (e.g., `myObject.f = window.fetch.bind(window);`)[12].\n\n4.  **Checking Property Descriptors:**\n    Before attempting to modify a property, you can check its descriptor using `Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(window, \'fetch\')` to see if it\'s writable or configurable. Some libraries, like `vConsole`, have implemented checks to avoid this error by verifying if the `fetch` property is writable before attempting to proxy it[2].\n\nIn summary, the \"Cannot set property fetch of #<Window>\" error means you\'re trying to directly overwrite a protected browser API. For testing, use dedicated mocking tools. For other interception needs, understand the limitations and consider alternative strategies that respect the browser\'s security and API design.\n\nSources:\n[1] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHqpkNqUNvz3pM-SkxjORD4r58P8EKeVWKM3nrE52Wu-Xdqy-i_a0dQnEwdpJrcW_hRDqLFF8RtOW9owrSjc-UBUzv29j4YHn0iKsKSYwFtlOTU8b6YosCdbcfXwueLYVsQc4crLb7VWqBX1bXu47sW1yp2kydTuz1v1a1fqShXB5R-Kq-qFfiqvOBZgh7G8fxUZoLaLM4eOnJVpwp2V2AP8pGFzTWvhrhzWWo186MGlg==)\n[2] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEIm1ouVH25BcM5qB6zKXxFNgYZQsLCzZM352Jc_k_3swIumdkq-eEfaxsrQ9K0RSf8QH6Otxs1rNa7RKA_bM-FQCwP-uWeixJsIUJgQzPtdB1zktioFAvSPrd2kDK5Zvty7M4Jq4XFX6E=)\n[3] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHWj1L4_D84HggxB2EIP1uQIrwFAYLsantaxhl8-sRRB2XsOlPJkSRqcQ8MCFlrQe5dcm8Ofq9q5bn0n6u8CnMzZwDXYt2FNvlTr8sn-Ji_1nIiLv8YLZzDTEW1WPXW7sPZCQmIfmM28kLk5znpUND-Qw0j5F41l0ahlVHQQKD5mpk7kduV0rwjD2H7Bjmf1fXL6ccm)\n[4] [medium.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGc2H_CQUKpT_vNMaje8sPWZju6mP3Z6QW5gHamrKYbg6yU2BVhA8w0auQf0NSgbqlpbavNCW6MJZE0cXm8lvowdbN1NoW44ufIu4dLLkWplm7vgjFKbMX2Ghpckx2WI-Vq-EJYtkxk3uN-U6dscCsmEOKdI7DUDDmrbeZOn_DxxFDYh3fR74QPoKsMRzc=)\n[5] [stevekinney.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHaWGhomfKZnB-JA6qaw33PlVjBEPhBVbKq2SQEfhTXL6akgwDbdnk3gEjUWzo21oLkcHs6ZP_1UAMrpFWq7XpNp3PXiab6qqhF9K0yU9k0rmz_AsWxL0gB5WidjlIQXj9foF1qE8Ajqf3e-re-or_s-w2i_sl8tz8KIRvO_QWNePRszlwl)\n[6] [swizec.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQF1AkTlKV6JDYhWrDP8Vqfa06nA7gWRiNlK0XllidC9QqlAO4TIy657EwEEfXL6FpUJ6XssAXOGF5GP-pUNn2XsqG0ac8QzRU9jel7KLsOM3r5nqY_3kVurjUSRC9d44JvoFT7g5YFAZaDNscp1ZPlOSuFg4FF-3a4-z7GYrUkUUw==)\n[7] [stackoverflow.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHnyh_m3fLaX0O5oqHHK5pZjbXf68KrRqePTlZxz4N-Nl2ktvT8zL0_4OtyIbqIxO