      url: "https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGw3RhuapTZ0i7TIVTK94oQDMAp9G0Nk6G1N88jxIMc3RYXyR8mhyMiGqKyANiZsK1ZIy8KJXWwI33QEtMqXcsAcEFkdPXIABhwBQB2D3_pwAGx4LUhZjDJIbol2HDpet1torFsFw=="
      title: "google.dev"
    }
    summary: "The error \"Uncaught TypeError: Cannot set property fetch of #<Window> which has only a getter\" on GitHub typically arises when a script attempts to redefine `window.fetch`, but `fetch` has been configured as a read-only getter property on the `Window` object. This prevents direct assignment to `window.fetch`.\n\nA prominent instance of this issue is found in the Tencent/vConsole library. Issue #662 on their GitHub repository details this exact problem[1][2]. The `vConsole` library, during its initialization, directly attempts to execute `window.fetch = ...`, leading to the `TypeError` when `fetch` is a read-only getter[1][3].\n\nThe proposed solution, already implemented in the `dev` branch of `vConsole`, involves checking if the property is writable using `Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor()` before attempting to proxy `fetch`. If the property is not writable, the `fetch` proxy is skipped[1][4]. This ensures that the network panel can still display XHR requests correctly without causing the error[1].\n\nThis error has also been reported by users of Google AI Studio when creating applications or using the Gemini API[5][6][7][8]. Users have encountered this `TypeError` along with \"Quota exceeded\" errors, indicating potential conflicts or underlying issues within that platform\'s environment[6][7].\n\nSources:\n[1] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGhOb67nMSOEapwV6g-zoF77g1VPR-6ZpBcgjbgaP_6YhSEADuibylkjwo9ChuQYyI20EzmWjePJUikM-0vZb7iFzmRrlJqW7A-p1xLOILQMDsUNAMBD49bjqaYcNhWxYokHOiCvnLHDAU=)\n[2] [ecosyste.ms](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHQdq8vXNCAKtmH170eWcPZqA0ZVCzPQ7s2DNv2YEKaEtZwe_q-OuU3EDYP1aF_q_PG23it6oQYNOGgkKreohqYcHcv2UmNiljq95oGr10xXTe9ORYTg2HOFtmboXWyuuhO5PhoXpfbO7GR-nEyM-ezjX1RpzJyn_UEJ1FlOSgWeXQHwLRxR5x7Fw==)\n[3] [gitee.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHk88IOPGHhHJhTHEsBDUsn5hM-IbqwPCIb1MibFgRes1BJHGtaWZgVE58fX-4QUIzPrwIqiSdRVnBXKpCqlv8eVXXDBpgghd0I3LnkwogWGN5DxbY6WYSjaFpzQzVs13rtqwtySG64DhIrN34n_j24_7S_lXDZ3fV3itX0Edhl31wuoNCsQ-4=)\n[4] [github.com](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFt6y3-H4wacohnUld1Ooo0uNCMQkfihSGZgTsndi43uDPeECAKNp9xWifT8r3FwTWlVR5dD7ydsTwWzAWrZc4lVIX0cFe5EZwJE9wVNS1KuKqGI-PQ1xNfNH7YG0H5mTv253k0DQ1fnnb2LANHsSLrp9KMA4jHMBTSMt3MxChT)\n[5] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQHDcICBVuswE7R-aa7fh_GRRx-G5uFF1Y6uvyX6NoJtWwLu7vRCLP0njn6k_pZYwaR43s2KeusPSAdqZAYxcGYNhHA9Ib7yT9ssEDyUum1RRxPKCNal8xAqTPog0CAb1FpTJ7zDKEpItCpsJ2M7R38e0lSd_EBAYWmUu44QKToE9K9BCYz-gQMUUaupd9eqrG0l_3ZZUzVZaO9NGCg55_tEjQM-p_Tu9BNz-vSQ14jwgg==)\n[6] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEiX5rNQgtwOFYOLhE8DQcfkeELtIN6vq8Lv2XxGzWmY6YCMaAWRwj2C-vbunzaWCVqAaKQLFrzvgCnvdlnSG17RK6W-grPRNw_jKq4gPaSfB41qXHqW0JAtiTho34gh5BhOWpY8jXO-0CUumYg9GGnnekYaAEc7wAdzvUDx52yIawpI3v0LwYDfohFxvJu9NFkmlWtYoBf2jKXRN7Pvnil8fQdZTFTJtJeXUCnQWM9Huo-ILlHN7zp5qQLXdUS3n5ZTSe6RnLE)\n[7] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFVGsUkX0O2GW97-6VdvTbSB3oYxgjuHRmD32YDNm3fZVAMZh8dpBuJ0xG3UWljQLw_tB5W9FeS60h6wQyw-TNgd7xHkDz8DvusOTC37L9fIjhyDMRHcpmlP3vkOO35JeDxrkWkevh3mBF2phJyQDYZRkKZlFFNycLcLmIq2Rz8Xo_R28NvIg4S2kOjTIqpQuvt7SCEBOoXPELqx-uWnIxbSImvcqyAmt6uCu4bp8OcMTJ84mWKz8zyBRuvJUFq-t7dMeo=)\n[8] [google.dev](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGw3RhuapTZ0i7TIVTK94oQDMAp9G0Nk6G1N88jxIMc3RYXyR8mhyMiGqKyANiZsK1ZIy8KJXWwI33QEtMqXcsAcEFkdPXIABhwBQB2D3_pwAGx4LUhZjDJIbol2HDpet1torFsFw==)"
